 increased.<br><br>Wizzies have gained 2k+ damage nukes, enchanters have dire charm, can charm level 49 mobs that can hit for 100's.  Same with necros and druids.  Most melee can be churning out 300-400 points a round.  Mages?  Their pets have lost power (they proc a lot fewer times than before, sword of runes don't work with them anymore.)  Mage nukes?  Post-50, a shammy or druid will out-nuke them.<br><br>Luclin brought some things, but no real improvements in damage that are not shared by pretty much all casters in general.<br><br>All and all, mages are really a class that verant dislikes.  A necro can twitch better than a mage with modrods, so basically the way you go on raids is your rep you earned, not due to class. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#E5E5E6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/uruanolikm.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ruanolik M</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>w4nn4b3!</span><br> <font color=#000033>(2/4/02 7:22:49 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/feqasylummagician.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=20.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Masters of summoning </span><hr size=1> And it's an honor.<br><br>I've never been denied a raid because of my class.  Ever.<br>People who know me send me tells for groups all the time.<br><br>Absor does have a point.  It does suck to be a mage, but a good mage is priceless.  I can give you a few examples without using CoH I helped a raid.  I bitch a lot.  I also work my ass off on raids, to make up for the very faults I bring up here.<br> <p><center><img src = "http://www.ilstu.edu/~djmorg2/RRlogo2.jpg"</center></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#D5D4D5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/udarkomen42.showPublicProfile?language=EN>DarkOmen42</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Boardaholic<